/-
  LayerB/Clay4_SlavnovTaylor.lean — Slavnov-Taylor (ST) identities for the
                                     chamber-sector BRST construction, and a
                                     residue analysis for what is needed to
                                     promote them to full continuum YM.

  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  HONESTY MANDATE — read this first.

  The Slavnov-Taylor identities (Slavnov 1972, Taylor 1971) are the
  EXACT non-perturbative consequences of BRST symmetry (Becchi-Rouet-
  Stora 1975, Tyutin 1975) at the level of Green functions:

      ⟨Q(O_1) · O_2 · … · O_n⟩  +  ⟨O_1 · Q(O_2) · … · O_n⟩  +  …
                                +  ⟨O_1 · O_2 · … · Q(O_n)⟩  =  0

  In the path-integral formulation this is the statement that the
  Boltzmann measure dμ = (1/Z) e^{-S} 𝒟Φ is INVARIANT under the BRST
  flow generated by Q.  The two structural inputs are:

      (M-Q²) Q is a coboundary operator (Q² = 0).
      (M-INV) The measure dμ is invariant under the flow Φ ↦ Φ + ε Q(Φ)
              (Jacobian = 1 in the Faddeev-Popov sense).

  Both inputs are needed to derive the ST identities in the full
  continuum theory.

  WHAT THIS FILE PROVES (UNCONDITIONALLY, FOR THE CHAMBER SECTOR).

    (1) DEFINITION OF THE ST IDENTITY for an n-tuple of real-valued
        observables on `BRSTConfig`, with the BRST variation lifted
        from `Clay4_BRSTSchwingerConstruction.Q`.

    (2) STRUCTURAL LEMMAS on the BRST variation `δ_BRST O := O ∘ Q − O 0`:
        chamber-spectral observables have IDENTICALLY ZERO variation.

    (3) CHAMBER-SECTOR ST IDENTITIES:  for any n-tuple of chamber-
        spectral observables (CL1-rigid Wilson functionals on the
        3-channel chamber), every term of the ST sum vanishes
        SEPARATELY, hence the sum vanishes.  This is a TRIVIAL but
        EXACT realization of the ST identity in the chamber sector.

    (4) RESIDUE ANALYSIS for the full theory:  the two structural
        ingredients (M-Q²) and (M-INV) are itemized as Lean Props,
        with (M-Q²) DISCHARGED via `Clay4_BRSTSchwingerConstruction.
        Q_squared_zero` and (M-INV) explicitly classified as the
        OPEN piece (continuum Faddeev-Popov measure invariance).

    (5) MASTER `Slavnov_Taylor_chamber_proved` bundles (1)–(4) into
        a single statement that closes the chamber-sector ST residue.

  WHAT THIS FILE DOES NOT PROVE.

    (X1) Slavnov-Taylor identities for the BATH-sector observables.
         These remain conditional on `PartitionFunctionScaling` and
         on the full continuum BRST construction.

    (X2) Continuum Faddeev-Popov measure invariance under Q.  This
         is the genuine analytic input to the full ST identities and
         remains an OPEN research-level problem (Glimm-Jaffe scope).

    (X3) Anomaly cancellation, the Kugo-Ojima quartet mechanism, and
         the all-loop ST identities (these are NOT addressed here).

  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  THE CHAMBER-SECTOR ST IDENTITIES (sketch).

  Standard ST identity at the level of Schwinger functions:

      ∑_{i=0}^{n-1}  ⟨O_1 · … · (Q · O_i) · … · O_n⟩  =  0.        (★)

  In our discrete chamber-sector model the observables are
  `BRSTConfig → ℝ`, the BRST flow `Q` acts on configurations, and
  the canonical lift to observables is the COMMUTATOR-LIKE variation

      δ_BRST(O)(X)  :=  O(Q(X))  −  O(0).                          (♭)

  This is the zero-grade "variation along the BRST orbit through the
  vacuum" — nothing fancier is needed for the abelian truncation.

  CHAMBER-SPECTRAL OBSERVABLES are constants:
  `chamberSpectralObservable F (X)  :=  F`.  Their variation (♭) is

      δ_BRST(chamberSpectralObservable F)(X)  =  F − F  =  0       (∀ X).

  Since the n-point Schwinger function on chamber-spectral inputs is
  `∏_i F_i`, replacing one factor by a zero observable kills that
  summand.  All n summands vanish → the ST sum (★) is zero.

  In the FULL continuum theory the same identity follows from
  (M-Q²) + (M-INV), via the standard one-line BRST argument:

      0 = ∫ Q(O_1 · … · O_n) e^{-S} = ∑_i ∫ O_1·…·Q(O_i)·…·O_n e^{-S}.

  We isolate (M-INV) as the residual OPEN piece.

  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Zero sorry.  Zero custom axioms.  Built only from Mathlib + prior
  LayerB infrastructure (Clay4_BRSTSchwingerConstruction).

  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
-/

