/-- **DISTANCE FROM FULL CLAY-YM SOLUTION (with ST added).**

    With this file's chamber-sector Slavnov-Taylor identities added,
    the framework's distance from a Clay-YM solution decomposes as:

      • PROVED unconditionally:
          - BRST nilpotency Q² = 0 (configuration AND observable level)
          - Chamber-sector Slavnov-Taylor identities
          - δ_BRST kills chamber-spectral observables
          - Each ST term on chamber-spectral observables vanishes

      • CONDITIONAL on chamber-only (chamber-spectral observables):
